column5: Well I have to say a big "THANK YOU"  to many people, Randy, John, Crumby, Mikey, Ryan, Zachary, Christian and Bill for helping Steve        ( Fishmaster) build the docks for the marina.  After many weeks of painstaking labor they are are finally done.  Buying Lumber, Steel, and hardware was only the beginning!  The planning and execution took many hours of time from all involved, from building the wood docks, locating and picking up barrels and steel to cutting and welding all the steel... Guys, it was a job you should all be very proud of...  14 slips, a boat launch dock and more to come... it is a far cry from a year ago when we started this adventure with naked water...  Congrats Steve on building what will definately be a fisherman's paradise!  Here is the finished product...
WOW that's really looking good Congrats to all involved Leechman
That's awesome!!  I bet the crappie like it too
looks great guys! cant wait to have a little free time to come out and see it.
looking good, some nice structure for crappies..
Thanks guys, it sure was a lot of work but worth it
